WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:11.150 align:middle line:90%


00:00:11.150 --> 00:00:12.090 align:middle line:90%
>> Bruce Lipton 2.

00:00:12.090 --> 00:00:12.890 align:middle line:90%
Take 1.

00:00:12.890 --> 00:00:13.957 align:middle line:90%
Marker.

00:00:13.957 --> 00:00:20.540 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:00:20.540 --> 00:00:23.030 align:middle line:90%
>> Who are you?

00:00:23.030 --> 00:00:25.790 align:middle line:10%
>> I am a happy guy.

00:00:25.790 --> 00:00:30.050 align:middle line:84%
And I had to learn that,
because maybe 40 years,

00:00:30.050 --> 00:00:31.130 align:middle line:90%
that was questionable.

00:00:31.130 --> 00:00:35.450 align:middle line:84%
But the last number of
years has been a joy.

00:00:35.450 --> 00:00:37.010 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, how did
you get that way?

00:00:37.010 --> 00:00:40.160 align:middle line:84%
>> First, understanding I was
responsible for whether I wanted

00:00:40.160 --> 00:00:41.322 align:middle line:90%
to be happy or not.

00:00:41.322 --> 00:00:42.530 align:middle line:90%
And then that was a decision.

00:00:42.530 --> 00:00:45.320 align:middle line:10%
Do you want this or do you
want-- oh, I want that one.

00:00:45.320 --> 00:00:48.590 align:middle line:90%
And then chose it.

00:00:48.590 --> 00:00:50.960 align:middle line:90%
It works.

00:00:50.960 --> 00:00:54.140 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, you write that "I
have come full circle from

00:00:54.140 --> 00:00:58.670 align:middle line:84%
a reductionist, scientific take
on life to a spiritual one,

00:00:58.670 --> 00:01:02.660 align:middle line:84%
also from an agnostic scientist
to a card-carrying mystic."

00:01:02.660 --> 00:01:03.590 align:middle line:90%
How so?

00:01:03.590 --> 00:01:05.920 align:middle line:90%
How did you get that way?

00:01:05.920 --> 00:01:09.820 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, for the most
formative years of my life,

00:01:09.820 --> 00:01:13.667 align:middle line:84%
you get a lot of wisdom from
so-called "spiritual people."

00:01:13.667 --> 00:01:16.000 align:middle line:84%
But as a kid, you could see
through it all of a sudden--

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:17.080 align:middle line:84%
And said, well,
the words are nice,

00:01:17.080 --> 00:01:18.910 align:middle line:84%
but their lives don't
even match anything

00:01:18.910 --> 00:01:20.200 align:middle line:90%
that they're talking about.

00:01:20.200 --> 00:01:22.480 align:middle line:84%
And there's some point
where, even as a kid,

00:01:22.480 --> 00:01:25.780 align:middle line:84%
it's like, how valid is that
statement if that person is

00:01:25.780 --> 00:01:27.050 align:middle line:90%
living this way?

00:01:27.050 --> 00:01:30.790 align:middle line:10%
And so at some point, I just
disregarded spirituality as not

00:01:30.790 --> 00:01:33.370 align:middle line:10%
really relevant because
it didn't serve those that

00:01:33.370 --> 00:01:36.790 align:middle line:10%
were telling me about it,
and dove into science,

00:01:36.790 --> 00:01:38.410 align:middle line:10%
because science was--

00:01:38.410 --> 00:01:40.750 align:middle line:10%
whatever was true in science
on this side of the planet

00:01:40.750 --> 00:01:42.458 align:middle line:10%
was true on the other
side of the planet.

00:01:42.458 --> 00:01:43.990 align:middle line:90%
So it was a pervasive truth.

00:01:43.990 --> 00:01:45.850 align:middle line:90%
And I love science.

00:01:45.850 --> 00:01:48.700 align:middle line:84%
And this has really
got me into the field.

00:01:48.700 --> 00:01:51.250 align:middle line:10%
And then I was most
fortunate to be

00:01:51.250 --> 00:01:53.590 align:middle line:10%
at the right place
at the right time

00:01:53.590 --> 00:01:56.650 align:middle line:10%
to work on stem cells, which
everybody hears about today,

00:01:56.650 --> 00:01:59.260 align:middle line:10%
but this was over 50 years ago.

00:01:59.260 --> 00:02:01.630 align:middle line:90%
And I was cloning stem cells.

00:02:01.630 --> 00:02:04.390 align:middle line:84%
And nobody really even
knew about stem cells,

00:02:04.390 --> 00:02:06.390 align:middle line:90%
but I was working with them.

00:02:06.390 --> 00:02:07.850 align:middle line:84%
And as I started
working with them,

00:02:07.850 --> 00:02:10.910 align:middle line:84%
I started to realize,
through my research,

00:02:10.910 --> 00:02:13.250 align:middle line:84%
that the fate of
the cells was not

00:02:13.250 --> 00:02:14.810 align:middle line:90%
controlled by their genetics.

00:02:14.810 --> 00:02:17.570 align:middle line:10%
The fate of the cell was
controlled by the environment

00:02:17.570 --> 00:02:19.130 align:middle line:10%
that they were in.

00:02:19.130 --> 00:02:22.940 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden, it takes
away the concept of genetics.

00:02:22.940 --> 00:02:25.470 align:middle line:10%
And I go, what's the
relevance of genetics?

00:02:25.470 --> 00:02:30.020 align:middle line:10%
So if I say, this trait is
under genetic control, what

00:02:30.020 --> 00:02:33.140 align:middle line:10%
that means in people's mind is
there's an automatic system,

00:02:33.140 --> 00:02:36.020 align:middle line:10%
a gene is going to turn on,
it's going to engage the trait,

00:02:36.020 --> 00:02:38.090 align:middle line:10%
and that's my
behavior or my life.

00:02:38.090 --> 00:02:40.317 align:middle line:84%
And then I go, well,
that's really interesting.

00:02:40.317 --> 00:02:41.900 align:middle line:84%
When we are teaching
that, what are we

00:02:41.900 --> 00:02:43.470 align:middle line:90%
teaching people about genetics?

00:02:43.470 --> 00:02:47.030 align:middle line:84%
I go, well, genes
control your life.

00:02:47.030 --> 00:02:48.560 align:middle line:84%
That, as far as we
know, you didn't

00:02:48.560 --> 00:02:50.640 align:middle line:90%
pick the genes you came with.

00:02:50.640 --> 00:02:53.150 align:middle line:84%
And if you don't like the
characteristics you have,

00:02:53.150 --> 00:02:55.220 align:middle line:90%
you can't change those genes.

00:02:55.220 --> 00:02:57.620 align:middle line:84%
And then we add on top
of that that the genes

00:02:57.620 --> 00:03:00.420 align:middle line:90%
turn on and off by themselves.

00:03:00.420 --> 00:03:02.800 align:middle line:90%
I say, what are we teaching?

00:03:02.800 --> 00:03:04.510 align:middle line:90%
Victimization.

00:03:04.510 --> 00:03:07.000 align:middle line:84%
You're a victim
of your heredity.

00:03:07.000 --> 00:03:11.170 align:middle line:84%
And it becomes really critical
because victim means powerless.

00:03:11.170 --> 00:03:13.930 align:middle line:10%
And if people are programmed
that their health is

00:03:13.930 --> 00:03:21.400 align:middle line:10%
beyond their control, then
they seek someone powerful that

00:03:21.400 --> 00:03:23.630 align:middle line:10%
will facilitate their health.

00:03:23.630 --> 00:03:25.420 align:middle line:10%
And so they give up power.

00:03:25.420 --> 00:03:27.250 align:middle line:10%
I'm powerless, so
I have no power,

00:03:27.250 --> 00:03:32.710 align:middle line:10%
but I accept what you say,
and that becomes my truth.

00:03:32.710 --> 00:03:36.010 align:middle line:10%
And then what, really,
the root comes down

00:03:36.010 --> 00:03:40.660 align:middle line:10%
to is understanding that
consciousness is translated

00:03:40.660 --> 00:03:44.500 align:middle line:10%
by the brain into
complementary chemistry, which

00:03:44.500 --> 00:03:50.170 align:middle line:10%
goes into the blood, and that
blood nourishes and instructs

00:03:50.170 --> 00:03:52.400 align:middle line:10%
50 trillion cells.

00:03:52.400 --> 00:03:55.480 align:middle line:10%
So the chemistry of the
blood is controlling

00:03:55.480 --> 00:03:58.390 align:middle line:10%
the genetics and the
behavior, but the chemistry

00:03:58.390 --> 00:03:59.300 align:middle line:10%
comes from the brain.

00:03:59.300 --> 00:04:01.840 align:middle line:90%
I go, yeah, but which chemistry?

00:04:01.840 --> 00:04:04.890 align:middle line:84%
Whatever picture is
held in the mind.

00:04:04.890 --> 00:04:09.710 align:middle line:84%
So for example, if
you say, I'm in love--

00:04:09.710 --> 00:04:11.740 align:middle line:90%
a picture of love--

00:04:11.740 --> 00:04:13.730 align:middle line:84%
I go, well that's a
beautiful picture.

00:04:13.730 --> 00:04:15.380 align:middle line:90%
All the romantic movie stuff.

00:04:15.380 --> 00:04:18.860 align:middle line:84%
And I go, if that's in your
mind, the chemistry that

00:04:18.860 --> 00:04:23.300 align:middle line:84%
comes from that love primarily
is dopamine, which is pleasure.

00:04:23.300 --> 00:04:24.860 align:middle line:90%
That's why we seek it.

00:04:24.860 --> 00:04:27.800 align:middle line:10%
Oxytocin is another
chemical released in love

00:04:27.800 --> 00:04:30.170 align:middle line:10%
because that bonds
me to the source.

00:04:30.170 --> 00:04:33.950 align:middle line:10%
Vasopressin is released,
because that chemical

00:04:33.950 --> 00:04:37.250 align:middle line:10%
makes me more attractive to my
partner so my partner stays.

00:04:37.250 --> 00:04:40.700 align:middle line:84%
And most importantly,
growth hormone

00:04:40.700 --> 00:04:42.317 align:middle line:90%
is released when you're in love.

00:04:42.317 --> 00:04:43.650 align:middle line:90%
And I go, what is that relevant?

00:04:43.650 --> 00:04:45.950 align:middle line:84%
I say, growth hormone is
what keeps you healthy

00:04:45.950 --> 00:04:47.750 align:middle line:90%
and maintains your biology.

00:04:47.750 --> 00:04:51.770 align:middle line:10%
So I say, so the chemical
cocktail translated from love

00:04:51.770 --> 00:04:55.250 align:middle line:10%
manifests an expression in the
body of health and harmony.

00:04:55.250 --> 00:04:58.760 align:middle line:10%
And that's why people, they say,
oh, look how in love they are.

00:04:58.760 --> 00:05:00.080 align:middle line:90%
See how they glow?

00:05:00.080 --> 00:05:01.510 align:middle line:90%
That glow is biology.

00:05:01.510 --> 00:05:03.260 align:middle line:84%
And I say, yeah, but
why are they glowing?

00:05:03.260 --> 00:05:06.770 align:middle line:84%
I say because the
environment of that chemistry

00:05:06.770 --> 00:05:09.470 align:middle line:90%
enhances vitality.

00:05:09.470 --> 00:05:12.710 align:middle line:84%
And I say, wait, same
person opens up their eyes

00:05:12.710 --> 00:05:14.720 align:middle line:84%
and sees something
that scares them,

00:05:14.720 --> 00:05:17.150 align:middle line:84%
you don't release
the love cocktail.

00:05:17.150 --> 00:05:19.760 align:middle line:84%
You release stress
hormones and factors

00:05:19.760 --> 00:05:21.280 align:middle line:90%
that affect the immune system.

00:05:21.280 --> 00:05:24.170 align:middle line:84%
And I go, this is a completely
different chemistry.

00:05:24.170 --> 00:05:28.760 align:middle line:84%
I go, oh, so if I have a
picture of love, I am healthy.

00:05:28.760 --> 00:05:32.810 align:middle line:84%
But then we find out
that a picture of fear

00:05:32.810 --> 00:05:36.600 align:middle line:84%
generates chemistry that
puts us into a protection.

00:05:36.600 --> 00:05:37.850 align:middle line:90%
That's what fear is all about.

00:05:37.850 --> 00:05:39.140 align:middle line:90%
I need protection.

00:05:39.140 --> 00:05:40.640 align:middle line:90%
And I say, so what?

00:05:40.640 --> 00:05:44.060 align:middle line:84%
I say, well, then, the chemicals
that are released in fear

00:05:44.060 --> 00:05:49.290 align:middle line:84%
redirect the body's
energy away from growth

00:05:49.290 --> 00:05:50.970 align:middle line:84%
and puts the energy
into everything

00:05:50.970 --> 00:05:52.780 align:middle line:90%
I need to escape the fear.

00:05:52.780 --> 00:05:54.330 align:middle line:84%
So I say, oh, so
what does it mean?

00:05:54.330 --> 00:05:57.180 align:middle line:84%
I say, the moment you
have fear, stress hormones

00:05:57.180 --> 00:05:59.920 align:middle line:84%
shut down the growth and
maintenance of the body.

00:05:59.920 --> 00:06:00.960 align:middle line:90%
I go, why?

00:06:00.960 --> 00:06:02.910 align:middle line:84%
Because why should
I expend energy

00:06:02.910 --> 00:06:06.090 align:middle line:84%
to grow the body if I'm being
chased by a saber toothed tiger?

00:06:06.090 --> 00:06:11.100 align:middle line:84%
I want all of the energy
available to escape the tiger.

00:06:11.100 --> 00:06:14.340 align:middle line:10%
So I redirect the
energy in the body

00:06:14.340 --> 00:06:16.560 align:middle line:10%
with the chemistry
that comes from fear,

00:06:16.560 --> 00:06:19.240 align:middle line:10%
redirects it not toward
maintenance of the body,

00:06:19.240 --> 00:06:22.350 align:middle line:10%
but redirects it toward
escaping the fear.

00:06:22.350 --> 00:06:25.620 align:middle line:84%
And I go, and most
important aspect of that

00:06:25.620 --> 00:06:30.910 align:middle line:84%
is that stress hormones
shut down the immune system.

00:06:30.910 --> 00:06:32.620 align:middle line:90%
So why should they do that?

00:06:32.620 --> 00:06:35.100 align:middle line:84%
And the answer is this--
because the immune system uses

00:06:35.100 --> 00:06:37.830 align:middle line:84%
so much energy that when
people are sick, sometimes,

00:06:37.830 --> 00:06:40.030 align:middle line:84%
they don't even have the
energy to get out of bed.

00:06:40.030 --> 00:06:41.640 align:middle line:90%
So then I put a situation here.

00:06:41.640 --> 00:06:45.120 align:middle line:84%
I say, you have a bacterial
infection, I always like to add,

00:06:45.120 --> 00:06:47.850 align:middle line:84%
possibly diarrhea
coming from this.

00:06:47.850 --> 00:06:50.225 align:middle line:84%
And you say, oh, I want my
immune system to handle this.

00:06:50.225 --> 00:06:51.850 align:middle line:84%
And I say, but at
the same time, you're

00:06:51.850 --> 00:06:55.230 align:middle line:84%
being chased by a
saber toothed tiger.

00:06:55.230 --> 00:06:57.240 align:middle line:84%
Where do you want
the energy to go?

00:06:57.240 --> 00:06:58.300 align:middle line:90%
You want to split it?

00:06:58.300 --> 00:06:59.820 align:middle line:90%
And I go, are you kidding me?

00:06:59.820 --> 00:07:01.980 align:middle line:10%
I put everything in to
running away from the tiger,

00:07:01.980 --> 00:07:04.530 align:middle line:10%
because if the
tiger catches you,

00:07:04.530 --> 00:07:07.870 align:middle line:10%
that bacteria is no longer
your problem at that moment.

00:07:07.870 --> 00:07:12.090 align:middle line:10%
So the idea is, stress hormones
shut down the immune system

00:07:12.090 --> 00:07:15.000 align:middle line:10%
to conserve energy
to escape the threat.

00:07:15.000 --> 00:07:18.720 align:middle line:84%
All of this sounds, on paper,
this is a beautiful mechanism.

00:07:18.720 --> 00:07:21.150 align:middle line:84%
And then I say, but when
was this mechanism designed?

00:07:21.150 --> 00:07:24.190 align:middle line:84%
I say hundreds of
thousands of years ago.

00:07:24.190 --> 00:07:27.510 align:middle line:84%
And I say, oh, then,
well, what fears

00:07:27.510 --> 00:07:29.310 align:middle line:90%
did we have 100,000 years ago?

00:07:29.310 --> 00:07:31.460 align:middle line:10%
I go, saber toothed tiger.

00:07:31.460 --> 00:07:32.260 align:middle line:90%
I go, so what?

00:07:32.260 --> 00:07:36.480 align:middle line:84%
I say, so I'm living in
growth, the happy part, feeding

00:07:36.480 --> 00:07:38.700 align:middle line:84%
my system, nourishing
and everything.

00:07:38.700 --> 00:07:40.230 align:middle line:90%
The tiger shows up.

00:07:40.230 --> 00:07:42.720 align:middle line:84%
The stress hormones are
released into the body.

00:07:42.720 --> 00:07:46.710 align:middle line:10%
That allows me to run like crazy
to get away from that tiger.

00:07:46.710 --> 00:07:50.580 align:middle line:84%
So maximum 10
minutes, I'm running.

00:07:50.580 --> 00:07:52.110 align:middle line:10%
I escape.

00:07:52.110 --> 00:07:53.010 align:middle line:90%
Now what?

00:07:53.010 --> 00:07:55.530 align:middle line:84%
I say, oh, I go back
to growth again.

00:07:55.530 --> 00:07:58.920 align:middle line:84%
So the inhibition
of body maintenance

00:07:58.920 --> 00:08:02.130 align:middle line:84%
and the inhibition of the immune
system is not a long-term thing.

00:08:02.130 --> 00:08:04.470 align:middle line:84%
It's supposed to
be just minutes.

00:08:04.470 --> 00:08:09.240 align:middle line:84%
But today's world,
stress is 24/7/365.

00:08:09.240 --> 00:08:13.260 align:middle line:10%
We were not designed
for prolonged inhibition

00:08:13.260 --> 00:08:16.020 align:middle line:10%
of the maintenance of
the body or prolonged

00:08:16.020 --> 00:08:19.800 align:middle line:10%
shutting down the immune system,
because this opens us up,

00:08:19.800 --> 00:08:22.480 align:middle line:10%
now, for infection and disease.

00:08:22.480 --> 00:08:25.650 align:middle line:10%
And so the interesting aspect
about that is since we have

00:08:25.650 --> 00:08:28.620 align:middle line:10%
programmed the public,
oh, disease is connected

00:08:28.620 --> 00:08:33.049 align:middle line:10%
to your genes, well,
let's-- a fact of science.

00:08:33.049 --> 00:08:37.270 align:middle line:10%
Less than 1% of disease
is connected to genes.

00:08:37.270 --> 00:08:41.559 align:middle line:84%
Over 90% of illness is
connected to environment

00:08:41.559 --> 00:08:45.507 align:middle line:84%
and our perception or
response to that environment.

00:08:45.507 --> 00:08:46.840 align:middle line:90%
And all of a sudden, I say, why?

00:08:46.840 --> 00:08:49.150 align:middle line:84%
Well, then, the
pathologies that affect us,

00:08:49.150 --> 00:08:52.330 align:middle line:84%
we're not genetically designed
to have those pathologies.

00:08:52.330 --> 00:08:54.610 align:middle line:90%
We are manifesting them.

00:08:54.610 --> 00:08:56.410 align:middle line:90%
There's no cancer gene--

00:08:56.410 --> 00:08:57.460 align:middle line:90%
a fact of life.

00:08:57.460 --> 00:09:00.850 align:middle line:10%
There is not one gene
that causes cancer.

00:09:00.850 --> 00:09:02.170 align:middle line:90%
You want to get cancer?

00:09:02.170 --> 00:09:04.360 align:middle line:84%
Oh, you have to
activate over 10.

00:09:04.360 --> 00:09:09.550 align:middle line:10%
Usually 15 to 20 different genes
must be activated simultaneously

00:09:09.550 --> 00:09:10.630 align:middle line:10%
to manifest a cancer.

00:09:10.630 --> 00:09:12.640 align:middle line:90%
I go, that many different genes?

00:09:12.640 --> 00:09:14.330 align:middle line:84%
If I said one gene
causes cancer,

00:09:14.330 --> 00:09:15.890 align:middle line:90%
you say, oh, one gene mutated.

00:09:15.890 --> 00:09:16.690 align:middle line:90%
I got cancer.

00:09:16.690 --> 00:09:20.018 align:middle line:90%
I go, it takes 10, 15, 20 genes.

00:09:20.018 --> 00:09:22.060 align:middle line:84%
I go, oh, well, then, all
of a sudden coincidence

00:09:22.060 --> 00:09:23.170 align:middle line:90%
is not part of it.

00:09:23.170 --> 00:09:27.910 align:middle line:84%
Now, there's an expression of
life contributing to the cancer.

00:09:27.910 --> 00:09:31.270 align:middle line:10%
And therefore, we end
up blaming the gene,

00:09:31.270 --> 00:09:33.500 align:middle line:10%
saying the genes cause cancer.

00:09:33.500 --> 00:09:36.860 align:middle line:10%
That disempowers us, because
as I said, I have no control.

00:09:36.860 --> 00:09:38.550 align:middle line:10%
The genes did it.

00:09:38.550 --> 00:09:41.300 align:middle line:84%
And then I go, but
the reality is,

00:09:41.300 --> 00:09:43.950 align:middle line:84%
there is no genetic
linkage to cancer.

00:09:43.950 --> 00:09:48.260 align:middle line:84%
Cancer is an inappropriate
response to an interpretation

00:09:48.260 --> 00:09:49.460 align:middle line:90%
of the world.

00:09:49.460 --> 00:09:52.430 align:middle line:84%
The environment they live
in, the perceptions they have

00:09:52.430 --> 00:09:54.600 align:middle line:90%
are manifesting in a cancer.

00:09:54.600 --> 00:09:56.750 align:middle line:84%
So what people
really need to hear

00:09:56.750 --> 00:10:00.450 align:middle line:84%
is, cancer is a
symptom, not a problem.

00:10:00.450 --> 00:10:01.250 align:middle line:90%
I go, so what?

00:10:01.250 --> 00:10:04.970 align:middle line:84%
I go, the way we've
created medicine

00:10:04.970 --> 00:10:08.570 align:middle line:84%
and pharmaceutical companies
is if you have a symptom,

