thing Bill is going to say

00:21:40.400 --> 00:21:43.970 align:middle line:10%
is, how can you
compare me to my dad?

00:21:43.970 --> 00:21:46.250 align:middle line:10%
I'm nothing like my dad.

00:21:46.250 --> 00:21:48.500 align:middle line:10%
And everyone in the
audience laughs.

00:21:48.500 --> 00:21:51.208 align:middle line:10%
And I say, they laugh
because they understand.

00:21:51.208 --> 00:21:52.250 align:middle line:10%
I said, what do you mean?

00:21:52.250 --> 00:21:56.640 align:middle line:10%
They all have seen somebody
deny their behavior.

00:21:56.640 --> 00:21:58.340 align:middle line:10%
And I go, why is it relevant?

00:21:58.340 --> 00:22:00.290 align:middle line:10%
Because everybody else
can see the behavior

00:22:00.290 --> 00:22:01.460 align:middle line:10%
that Bill is expressing.

00:22:01.460 --> 00:22:02.990 align:middle line:10%
Who's the one that can't see it?

00:22:02.990 --> 00:22:03.980 align:middle line:10%
Bill.

00:22:03.980 --> 00:22:04.910 align:middle line:10%
Why not?

00:22:04.910 --> 00:22:07.740 align:middle line:10%
Because the reason he's
playing that behavior,

00:22:07.740 --> 00:22:10.550 align:middle line:10%
he's not paying attention.

00:22:10.550 --> 00:22:11.910 align:middle line:90%
So what's the point?

00:22:11.910 --> 00:22:12.890 align:middle line:90%
The point is this.

00:22:12.890 --> 00:22:17.390 align:middle line:84%
95% of your life is not coming
from the wishes and desires

00:22:17.390 --> 00:22:19.910 align:middle line:84%
of the creative mind,
which is busy thinking.

00:22:19.910 --> 00:22:21.465 align:middle line:84%
It's going to come
from the programs.

00:22:21.465 --> 00:22:23.090 align:middle line:84%
And I go, yeah, but
the programs mainly

00:22:23.090 --> 00:22:23.990 align:middle line:90%
didn't even come from you.

00:22:23.990 --> 00:22:25.380 align:middle line:10%
They came from somebody else.

00:22:25.380 --> 00:22:27.770 align:middle line:10%
You downloaded somebody
else's behavior.

00:22:27.770 --> 00:22:30.140 align:middle line:10%
And if that behavior
doesn't support

00:22:30.140 --> 00:22:32.970 align:middle line:10%
your program and
your wishes, too bad,

00:22:32.970 --> 00:22:34.970 align:middle line:10%
because that's the program
that's going to play,

00:22:34.970 --> 00:22:36.660 align:middle line:10%
whether you see it or not.

00:22:36.660 --> 00:22:40.790 align:middle line:10%
And this is why Bill cannot
see he's like his dad.

00:22:40.790 --> 00:22:42.800 align:middle line:10%
And the most profound ending--

00:22:42.800 --> 00:22:43.610 align:middle line:10%
sorry.

00:22:43.610 --> 00:22:44.300 align:middle line:10%
Save it.

00:22:44.300 --> 00:22:45.140 align:middle line:90%
Big drum roll.

00:22:45.140 --> 00:22:46.590 align:middle line:90%
Profound ending.

00:22:46.590 --> 00:22:47.390 align:middle line:90%
Is this.

00:22:47.390 --> 00:22:49.940 align:middle line:90%
We are all Bill.

00:22:49.940 --> 00:22:53.527 align:middle line:84%
Every one of us is
doing this every day.

00:22:53.527 --> 00:22:54.860 align:middle line:90%
And I go, what is the relevance?

00:22:54.860 --> 00:22:56.760 align:middle line:84%
And now, we put the
story into conclusion.

00:22:56.760 --> 00:22:57.560 align:middle line:90%
It's this.

00:22:57.560 --> 00:23:01.430 align:middle line:10%
Creative mind-- I want love, I
want health, I want happiness,

00:23:01.430 --> 00:23:03.920 align:middle line:10%
I want a great job, I
want money, I want this.

00:23:03.920 --> 00:23:05.967 align:middle line:10%
I go, that's good creativity.

00:23:05.967 --> 00:23:07.550 align:middle line:84%
I say, so, in the
morning, you wake up

00:23:07.550 --> 00:23:10.340 align:middle line:84%
and you say, today,
I'm going to go

00:23:10.340 --> 00:23:12.470 align:middle line:84%
get those things that my
creative mind has just

00:23:12.470 --> 00:23:13.400 align:middle line:90%
thought of.

00:23:13.400 --> 00:23:17.030 align:middle line:84%
And then you go out to
