it, it's going to be great.

01:19:23.580 --> 01:19:25.050 align:middle line:90%
Must we follow through on it?

01:19:25.050 --> 01:19:26.310 align:middle line:90%
Well, no.

01:19:26.310 --> 01:19:28.170 align:middle line:10%
Other civilizations
have been here

01:19:28.170 --> 01:19:29.970 align:middle line:10%
and disappeared in the past.

01:19:29.970 --> 01:19:30.780 align:middle line:90%
Why?

01:19:30.780 --> 01:19:33.300 align:middle line:84%
They never
successfully completed

01:19:33.300 --> 01:19:36.060 align:middle line:90%
the last stage of that.

01:19:36.060 --> 01:19:37.960 align:middle line:90%
They collapsed.

01:19:37.960 --> 01:19:42.010 align:middle line:10%
Whether it's Atlantis,
Lemuria, or wherever one

01:19:42.010 --> 01:19:44.020 align:middle line:10%
you find from ancient history--

01:19:44.020 --> 01:19:45.730 align:middle line:10%
that is not in our
history actually,

01:19:45.730 --> 01:19:47.380 align:middle line:10%
because, those
civilizations existed

01:19:47.380 --> 01:19:49.990 align:middle line:10%
before our modern history--

01:19:49.990 --> 01:19:51.100 align:middle line:10%
the relevance is what?

01:19:51.100 --> 01:19:53.880 align:middle line:10%
We are in the same position.

01:19:53.880 --> 01:19:56.520 align:middle line:10%
Are we going to make
it as a civilization?

01:19:56.520 --> 01:20:00.390 align:middle line:10%
At this very moment, 50/50.

01:20:00.390 --> 01:20:01.620 align:middle line:10%
I have no idea.

01:20:01.620 --> 01:20:07.580 align:middle line:10%
We have the potential, but we
may not realize our potential.

01:20:07.580 --> 01:20:12.480 align:middle line:10%
>> Do you think that AI,
artificial intelligence,

01:20:12.480 --> 01:20:15.000 align:middle line:10%
is in that path?

01:20:15.000 --> 01:20:18.810 align:middle line:10%
>> It is, to a certain extent,
if we understand what it's to be

01:20:18.810 --> 01:20:20.220 align:middle line:10%
used for.

01:20:20.220 --> 01:20:21.600 align:middle line:10%
And the answer is this.

01:20:21.600 --> 01:20:24.150 align:middle line:10%
Right now, we've been programmed
with the cultural beliefs

01:20:24.150 --> 01:20:26.622 align:middle line:10%
that we are the workers that
empower what's going on,

01:20:26.622 --> 01:20:28.080 align:middle line:10%
and you go out
there and you do all

01:20:28.080 --> 01:20:29.460 align:middle line:10%
this mechanical, physical work.

01:20:29.460 --> 01:20:30.420 align:middle line:10%
And you get a reward.

01:20:30.420 --> 01:20:31.380 align:middle line:10%
You get a paycheck.

01:20:31.380 --> 01:20:33.990 align:middle line:10%
And some people just
scrape by with enough

01:20:33.990 --> 01:20:35.130 align:middle line:10%
of a reward to survive.

01:20:35.130 --> 01:20:36.840 align:middle line:10%
Other people
accumulate some money

01:20:36.840 --> 01:20:39.430 align:middle line:10%
and can do things
with it like that.

01:20:39.430 --> 01:20:43.770 align:middle line:84%
And so the issue is, is
artificial intelligence

01:20:43.770 --> 01:20:45.690 align:middle line:90%
going to replace humans?

01:20:45.690 --> 01:20:48.690 align:middle line:10%
And the answer-- that would
be one of the stupidest

01:20:48.690 --> 01:20:50.970 align:middle line:10%
ideas in the universe.

01:20:50.970 --> 01:20:52.390 align:middle line:10%
I say, why?

01:20:52.390 --> 01:20:56.380 align:middle line:10%
Because if I say, then why
are we here at this time?

01:20:56.380 --> 01:20:59.070 align:middle line:10%
And the answer is
because we are creators.

01:20:59.070 --> 01:21:03.550 align:middle line:10%
We can create the mess we've
done, which we've done.

01:21:03.550 --> 01:21:06.300 align:middle line:10%
But as we know from
the honeymoon effect,

01:21:06.300 --> 01:21:08.430 align:middle line:10%
we can manifest Heaven on Earth.

01:21:08.430 --> 01:21:14.470 align:middle line:10%
Do I want to turn over the joy
and love and happiness of heaven

01:21:14.470 --> 01:21:16.430 align:middle line:10%
on earth and let a
machine experience it?

01:21:16.430 --> 01:21:17.230 align:middle line:10%
Hell no.

01:21:17.230 --> 01:21:18.980 align:middle line:10%
What the hell do I
care about the machine?

01:21:18.980 --> 01:21:19.930 align:middle line:10%
It's me.

01:21:19.930 --> 01:21:23.907 align:middle line:10%
So when we focus on AI, you
take yourself out of the picture

01:21:23.907 --> 01:21:25.990 align:middle line:10%
and then all of a sudden,
you see a machine world.

01:21:25.990 --> 01:21:27.790 align:middle line:10%
People are part machines.

01:21:27.790 --> 01:21:31.120 align:middle line:10%
It's like, man, you
missed the story.

01:21:31.120 --> 01:21:33.400 align:middle line:10%
We're the creators.

01:21:33.400 --> 01:21:36.490 align:middle line:10%
You don't replace the
creator with a machine.

01:21:36.490 --> 01:21:37.990 align:middle line:10%
The creator does what?

01:21:37.990 --> 01:21:40.510 align:middle line:10%
If the machines
support us, it gives me

01:21:40.510 --> 01:21:44.390 align:middle line:10%
more free, creative
opportunities.

01:21:44.390 --> 01:21:48.640 align:middle line:10%
So I look to AI as to enhance
my experience of Heaven

01:21:48.640 --> 01:21:52.330 align:middle line:10%
on Earth, not to replace my
experience of Heaven on Earth.

01:21:52.330 --> 01:21:56.830 align:middle line:10%
And that's where AI's
got the whole idea wrong.

01:21:56.830 --> 01:21:58.838 align:middle line:10%
What value would humans have?

01:21:58.838 --> 01:22:00.130 align:middle line:10%
Oh, the machine will do it all.

01:22:00.130 --> 01:22:03.850 align:middle line:10%
So then what the heck
are you going to do?

01:22:03.850 --> 01:22:08.790 align:middle line:10%
And the point is, we
are here for a reason.

01:22:08.790 --> 01:22:09.940 align:middle line:10%
We don't have to be here.

01:22:09.940 --> 01:22:12.260 align:middle line:10%
We've been lost nearly--

01:22:12.260 --> 01:22:16.070 align:middle line:10%
all organisms have been lost
nearly five times in history

01:22:16.070 --> 01:22:17.870 align:middle line:10%
through mass extinctions.

01:22:17.870 --> 01:22:19.920 align:middle line:10%
But we're still here.

01:22:19.920 --> 01:22:22.650 align:middle line:10%
And the idea is there
was a mission statement.

01:22:22.650 --> 01:22:26.010 align:middle line:10%
And the mission statement,
when realized by humans,

01:22:26.010 --> 01:22:28.950 align:middle line:10%
is experiencing what is
called Heaven on Earth.

01:22:28.950 --> 01:22:30.810 align:middle line:10%
And it's beautiful
because there's no one

01:22:30.810 --> 01:22:32.460 align:middle line:10%
definition of Heaven on Earth.

01:22:32.460 --> 01:22:34.350 align:middle line:10%
You can ask 10 people
their definitions.

01:22:34.350 --> 01:22:36.790 align:middle line:10%
You're going to
get 10 definitions.

01:22:36.790 --> 01:22:39.840 align:middle line:10%
So the conclusion is, it's
not just heaven on earth.

01:22:39.840 --> 01:22:42.950 align:middle line:10%
It's what you want.

01:22:42.950 --> 01:22:45.590 align:middle line:10%
If I say to you, tell me
your vision of Heaven,

01:22:45.590 --> 01:22:50.390 align:middle line:10%
it will be your interpretation,
based on your life experiences,

01:22:50.390 --> 01:22:54.050 align:middle line:10%
because that's what you can
draw from, of how would you

01:22:54.050 --> 01:22:56.150 align:middle line:10%
like to put those
experiences in a situation

01:22:56.150 --> 01:22:59.210 align:middle line:10%
where you will enjoy them?

01:22:59.210 --> 01:23:01.610 align:middle line:10%
And different people have
different experiences.

01:23:01.610 --> 01:23:03.920 align:middle line:10%
It's not all the same.

01:23:03.920 --> 01:23:06.470 align:middle line:10%
Like, if someone
was talking about--

01:23:06.470 --> 01:23:08.660 align:middle line:10%
you ask a hunter,
what is Heaven?

01:23:08.660 --> 01:23:11.850 align:middle line:10%
And that hunter says, oh, I
go out every day duck hunting

01:23:11.850 --> 01:23:12.650 align:middle line:10%
in the morning.

01:23:12.650 --> 01:23:15.830 align:middle line:10%
I go out in the boat and I
shoot ducks all day long.

01:23:15.830 --> 01:23:18.920 align:middle line:10%
I go, oh, so your heaven
is shooting ducks,

01:23:18.920 --> 01:23:22.665 align:middle line:10%
so I guess your heaven is
hell for ducks, isn't it?

01:23:22.665 --> 01:23:28.850 align:middle line:10%
[LAUGHTER] I don't want to
be a duck in your Heaven.

01:23:28.850 --> 01:23:30.900 align:middle line:10%
And the simple reality
is, why are we here?

01:23:30.900 --> 01:23:34.220 align:middle line:10%
Because it's the
versatility of a system

01:23:34.220 --> 01:23:37.910 align:middle line:10%
to create all the art,
the music, the writing,

01:23:37.910 --> 01:23:40.760 align:middle line:10%
the sculptures, the
buildings, the technology.

01:23:40.760 --> 01:23:42.720 align:middle line:90%
We are creators.

01:23:42.720 --> 01:23:45.460 align:middle line:84%
If you want to let go
and die and give it to--

01:23:45.460 --> 01:23:46.260 align:middle line:90%
we can walk away.

01:23:46.260 --> 01:23:47.460 align:middle line:90%
The machine's going to create.

01:23:47.460 --> 01:23:48.260 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to die.

01:23:48.260 --> 01:23:52.480 align:middle line:10%
And I go, then why the hell were
you here in the first place?

01:23:52.480 --> 01:23:54.810 align:middle line:10%
And the idea is, from
my personal experience--

01:23:54.810 --> 01:23:58.410 align:middle line:10%
never experiencing it
until I was much older,

01:23:58.410 --> 01:24:03.810 align:middle line:10%
over 50, when I really had
an experience of love that

01:24:03.810 --> 01:24:09.630 align:middle line:10%
truly manifests that
I live in Heaven.

01:24:09.630 --> 01:24:12.960 align:middle line:10%
I wake up every day going,
oh, my god, I'm still here.

01:24:12.960 --> 01:24:19.170 align:middle line:10%
There's another day of social,
loving, physical, mental

01:24:19.170 --> 01:24:23.780 align:middle line:10%
expression-- fun, love,
living in a garden.

01:24:23.780 --> 01:24:26.750 align:middle line:10%
And once I understood
that, the first 50

01:24:26.750 --> 01:24:30.380 align:middle line:10%
years of the mechanism of Bruce
being the machine creating

01:24:30.380 --> 01:24:34.550 align:middle line:10%
all this kind of stuff, had
no real value until the day

01:24:34.550 --> 01:24:39.680 align:middle line:10%
I recognized the value of love,
because love is a destination.

01:24:39.680 --> 01:24:42.320 align:middle line:10%
And that's pretty interesting,
because today's world

01:24:42.320 --> 01:24:45.860 align:middle line:10%
is preoccupied with fear,
which is the complete opposite.

01:24:45.860 --> 01:24:47.900 align:middle line:10%
And until you get
out of this fear,

01:24:47.900 --> 01:24:51.260 align:middle line:10%
you are not going to
manage your evolution.

01:24:51.260 --> 01:24:55.950 align:middle line:10%
You're being manipulated by
a belief that's not real.

01:24:55.950 --> 01:24:59.460 align:middle line:10%
And as a result,
that's the illusion

01:24:59.460 --> 01:25:01.120 align:middle line:10%
that Einstein talked about.

01:25:01.120 --> 01:25:02.970 align:middle line:10%
This reality is an illusion.

01:25:02.970 --> 01:25:04.200 align:middle line:10%
You want a different reality?

01:25:04.200 --> 01:25:06.300 align:middle line:10%
Change your mind.

01:25:06.300 --> 01:25:08.640 align:middle line:10%
And all of a sudden, it
says, you are powerful.

01:25:08.640 --> 01:25:10.380 align:middle line:10%
You're not a victim.

01:25:10.380 --> 01:25:13.340 align:middle line:84%
If you believe you're
a victim, you are.

01:25:13.340 --> 01:25:15.800 align:middle line:90%
Oh, believe.

01:25:15.800 --> 01:25:18.680 align:middle line:10%
The book-- "The
Biology of Belief."

01:25:18.680 --> 01:25:20.550 align:middle line:84%
What the heck is that
about-- oh, my god,

01:25:20.550 --> 01:25:22.175 align:middle line:84%
that's about what we
just talked about.

01:25:22.175 --> 01:25:25.620 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

01:25:25.620 --> 01:25:26.420 align:middle line:90%
>> Bravo.

01:25:26.420 --> 01:25:27.690 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, that's great.

01:25:27.690 --> 01:25:28.490 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

01:25:28.490 --> 01:25:30.865 align:middle line:84%
I mean Bruce, unless there's
something else that you feel

01:25:30.865 --> 01:25:32.840 align:middle line:84%
like, yeah, we need
to say this part,

01:25:32.840 --> 01:25:35.630 align:middle line:84%
it's so relevant to what you're
doing, then I feel like--

01:25:35.630 --> 01:25:38.540 align:middle line:84%
>> I think you have a project
that I don't want to be involved

01:25:38.540 --> 01:25:40.310 align:middle line:90%
with.

01:25:40.310 --> 01:25:42.590 align:middle line:84%
I think you want to take
this down to five minutes

01:25:42.590 --> 01:25:45.770 align:middle line:84%
and I say, God bless
you for that effort.

01:25:45.770 --> 01:25:46.860 align:middle line:90%
>> I think it's mutual--

01:25:46.860 --> 01:25:48.990 align:middle line:84%
>> I have no idea
how you do that.

01:25:48.990 --> 01:25:50.420 align:middle line:90%
But that's a beautiful part.

01:25:50.420 --> 01:25:52.370 align:middle line:90%
OK, I leave.

01:25:52.370 --> 01:25:54.810 align:middle line:84%
And then sometime in the
future, you show me--

01:25:54.810 --> 01:25:57.140 align:middle line:84%
you see this three and a
half minute piece of you?

01:25:57.140 --> 01:26:00.260 align:middle line:10%
Everything you said
in an hour and a half

01:26:00.260 --> 01:26:03.060 align:middle line:10%
is in that three minutes.

01:26:03.060 --> 01:26:03.860 align:middle line:90%
Good job.

01:26:03.860 --> 01:26:06.480 align:middle line:90%


01:26:06.480 --> 01:26:07.280 align:middle line:10%
>> Oh, no.

01:26:07.280 --> 01:26:11.570 align:middle line:10%
I see you in different parts of
the series, not just like, Bruce

01:26:11.570 --> 01:26:13.500 align:middle line:10%
and then that's it.

01:26:13.500 --> 01:26:15.522 align:middle line:10%
Because you said,
you've covered so much.

01:26:15.522 --> 01:26:16.980 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, well that
was the problem.

01:26:16.980 --> 01:26:18.230 align:middle line:90%
There's three different books.

01:26:18.230 --> 01:26:20.910 align:middle line:84%
The first book is the biology
of how you create your own life.

01:26:20.910 --> 01:26:23.250 align:middle line:84%
The second book
is, well, if belief

01:26:23.250 --> 01:26:24.870 align:middle line:84%
is creating our life
experience, what

01:26:24.870 --> 01:26:27.390 align:middle line:84%
is the consequence
of mass belief?

01:26:27.390 --> 01:26:29.490 align:middle line:90%
Mass manifestation.

01:26:29.490 --> 01:26:31.440 align:middle line:90%
So that's spontaneous evolution.

01:26:31.440 --> 01:26:33.600 align:middle line:84%
It says, and look
what we created?

01:26:33.600 --> 01:26:34.650 align:middle line:90%
Self-destruction.

01:26:34.650 --> 01:26:37.650 align:middle line:90%
So that requires a new creation.

01:26:37.650 --> 01:26:39.570 align:middle line:84%
And the third one
was the honeymoon.

01:26:39.570 --> 01:26:42.510 align:middle line:90%
Because the honeymoon was, how--

01:26:42.510 --> 01:26:46.470 align:middle line:84%
besides yourself, we are
driven to be in community,

01:26:46.470 --> 01:26:50.060 align:middle line:84%
and the first community
is two people.

01:26:50.060 --> 01:26:53.180 align:middle line:10%
And if two people are
in love and two people

01:26:53.180 --> 01:26:56.220 align:middle line:10%
are living in harmony
and creativity,

01:26:56.220 --> 01:26:58.020 align:middle line:10%
well they're
enjoying this planet

01:26:58.020 --> 01:27:01.920 align:middle line:10%
like, oh, my god, the
garden that it really was.

01:27:01.920 --> 01:27:07.200 align:middle line:10%
And it's really interesting
because, by definition, a garden

01:27:07.200 --> 01:27:09.120 align:middle line:10%
is the height of community.

01:27:09.120 --> 01:27:12.510 align:middle line:84%
Every organism in that garden
is supporting the existence

01:27:12.510 --> 01:27:14.280 align:middle line:90%
of this beautiful garden.

01:27:14.280 --> 01:27:17.490 align:middle line:84%
And then it's
community and harmony.

01:27:17.490 --> 01:27:19.710 align:middle line:10%
And then humans
step into the garden

01:27:19.710 --> 01:27:22.170 align:middle line:10%
and put their big feet
all over everything,

01:27:22.170 --> 01:27:23.850 align:middle line:10%
are destroying things.

01:27:23.850 --> 01:27:26.400 align:middle line:84%
It's the belief that we
can do whatever we want.

01:27:26.400 --> 01:27:27.780 align:middle line:90%
No, it's a garden.

01:27:27.780 --> 01:27:30.990 align:middle line:10%
And as the Indigenous people
of this planet are still here

01:27:30.990 --> 01:27:34.170 align:middle line:10%
to help us-- because
we have forgotten--

01:27:34.170 --> 01:27:37.000 align:middle line:10%
that we are gardeners.

01:27:37.000 --> 01:27:40.240 align:middle line:84%
But we've been exploiting
it and taking it apart.

01:27:40.240 --> 01:27:43.690 align:middle line:10%
And the net result is we
are now looking at doomsday

01:27:43.690 --> 01:27:45.290 align:middle line:10%
not in thousand years.

01:27:45.290 --> 01:27:46.840 align:middle line:10%
We're talking within a century.

01:27:46.840 --> 01:27:49.000 align:middle line:10%
Human civilization
will be doomed

01:27:49.000 --> 01:27:52.870 align:middle line:10%
unless we change how we
relate to the environment,

01:27:52.870 --> 01:27:54.490 align:middle line:10%
because the first
thing is this--

01:27:54.490 --> 01:27:57.760 align:middle line:10%
we evolved from the garden.

01:27:57.760 --> 01:28:01.450 align:middle line:84%
We were never separate
from the garden.

01:28:01.450 --> 01:28:03.820 align:middle line:84%
And the idea that we could
stand outside and tell

01:28:03.820 --> 01:28:06.970 align:middle line:84%
the garden what to do is
like, oh, human hubris.

01:28:06.970 --> 01:28:08.260 align:middle line:90%
We're so smart.

01:28:08.260 --> 01:28:10.990 align:middle line:84%
Well, we're so smart then how
come we're facing a sixth mass

01:28:10.990 --> 01:28:11.800 align:middle line:90%
extinction?

01:28:11.800 --> 01:28:16.120 align:middle line:90%


01:28:16.120 --> 01:28:17.560 align:middle line:90%
>> And on that note.

01:28:17.560 --> 01:28:19.410 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

